name: Rudy Giuliani
subject: Now, my primary residence could be “seized”
body: BREAKING: A federal judge is now considering… ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏ ͏  Dear Friend, On October 22, a federal judge decreed that I had 7days to hand over my home in New York – as well as my only car and sentimentalkeepsakes and heartfelt gifts that I collected over the span of 80 years. Ithought that would be the end of the damage… But with the election rightaround the corner, Kamala’s Deep State truly wants to ruin me with all they’vegot. They’re now considering dealing one final blow to me. A judge may noworder me to give up my remaining home in Florida – my primary residence. As mylawyer inquired: do they truly want me homeless? Over the last few days, we’veheard ridiculous claims about President Trump being a “fascist.” Let me tellyou what fascism is… Fascism is weaponizing the legal system to punish yourpolitical opponents. Fascism is having your home taken from you. Fascism istaking the law license away from your opponent’s lawyer. Fascism is trying toturn your enemies into political prisoners. I am living through theDemocrats’ fascism right now. I sincerely pray that freedom, justice, and thetruth prevail on Tuesday, November 5 – or the damage done to me will spreadlike wildfire to the rest of our great Republic. But, as I wrote to you in anearlier letter, the Bible reminds us that our earthly possessions will alwaysfade, but greater “heavenly treasures” await us. The pursuit of truth,freedom, and justice are worth infinitely more than a car or a home.Possessions come and go, but I couldNEVER SURRENDER my fight for freedom andfor what I know to betrue. I would be tone deaf if I didn’t acknowledge thattimes are tough right now for all Americans, not just me, so please stopreading here if you cannot give at this time. But funding my Legal DefenseTrust is my last remaining hope of fighting for my freedom and for the libertyand justice of all Americans. So, if you can, and, seriously, only if you can,please make a contribution to my Legal Defense Trust – the Rudy GiulianiFreedom Fund – as I keep fighting for my freedom and justice as Kamala’s DeepState tries to JAIL me for life. CONTRIBUTE $25 CONTRIBUTE $50 CONTRIBUTE$100 CONTRIBUTE $250 CONTRIBUTE $500 CONTRIBUTE OTHER AMOUNT Thank you andGod bless you, Rudy Giuliani Rudy Giuliani Freedom Fund Paid for by RudyGiuliani Freedom Fund Legal Defense Trust Conservative Liberty Wire PO Box1188 Fort Collins, CO 80522 unsubscribe |manage data preferences

name: Mark Warner
subject: I’ve spent a lot of time with Tim Kaine
body: Derek, I’ve had the honor of being Tim Kaine’s friend since we met at HarvardLaw School in 1980. For over 40 years, I’ve watched him wholeheartedly serveVirginia, first as mayor of Richmond, then as my Lieutenant Governor, andlater Governor, before serving together in the United States Senate. Thismeans I’ve spent a lot of time with Tim and gathered plenty of intel on him.So as I sat down to write this email asking you to support Senator Kaine’s re-election campaign, I found myself wondering exactly what I should say to youto assure you that Tim is the right choice to represent Virginia in Congress.And then it dawned on me: I want to tell you the top 3 things that annoy methe most about Tim Kaine. First off, Tim is way too nice! As a former civilrights attorney and missionary, he’s spent his entire career committed tosocial justice, being driven by the value of kindness and the belief that itcan change peoples’ lives. And he’s a genuinely good guy on top of that.Second, he’s ridiculously good at playing the harmonica. Seriously, he carriesthem in his briefcase, just in case a jam session breaks out on the Senatefloor. Third and finally, and I’ve said this before, he’s a deeply optimisticperson. Sometimes I can be a glass half-empty kind of guy, but Tim’s alwaysseems about ⅔ full. We need someone like Tim Kaine in the Senate. Tim’s valueof kindness and decency is what drives his undying dedication to serving thepeople of Virginia. And in a Congress plagued by partisan division, Tim’srelentless optimism keeps him from giving up in the crucial fights to protectvoting rights, safeguard a woman’s right to choose, and more. Now theharmonica… that one might not always translate to his work as a Senator, it’sjust really great to watch. The thing is, Tim’s seat could very well determineif the GOP takes control on Tuesday. Republicans are working overtime to ousthim and take back control of the Senate. So I’m asking you today if you cansplit a $5 donation between my campaign and Tim Kaine’s so we can send him,his kindness, impressive harmonica playing, and optimism back to the Senate?https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?amount=5&refcode;=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1 Ifyou've saved your payment information with ActBlue Express, your donation willbe automatically split between Tim Kaine and Mark Warner: EXPRESS DONATE $5https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?express_lane=true&amount;=5&refcode;=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1EXPRESS DONATE $10 https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?express_lane=true&amount;=10&refcode;=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1EXPRESS DONATE $25 https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?express_lane=true&amount;=25&refcode;=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1EXPRESS DONATE $50 https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?express_lane=true&amount;=50&refcode;=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1EXPRESS DONATE $100 https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?express_lane=true&amount;=100&refcode;=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1DONATE OTHER https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?express_lane_other=true&refcode;=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1I know Tim very well, and I know he’s not done building a Virginia that worksfor all. Help re-elect Senator Kaine and defend our Democratic Senate majorityby splitting a contribution today >>> https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?amount=5&refcode;=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1 Thankyou, Mark Contribute https://secure.actblue.com/donate/mw-email-240528-kaine?refcode=MW_ATA_EM_FR_Kainesplit_241101_T1_1 ---- Friends ofMark Warner 1490-5A Quarterpath Road #213 Williamsburg, VA 23185 United StatesTo unsubscribe, go to: unsubscribe: https://secure.ngpvan.com/p/2Buh_-FbSkCM8ZUa-iiD5Q2?unsubscribedata=TR0MtEc6xaoG7SLnux5O2KQbXLJPt2%2FuNy2jUZMmKgz%2BD2innsxDKR3omYmOXCo6%2FJh44r3DrCgxLGhQeJmQLh8khb6WuNiorL%2BgBo%2Fysa3ffagHAVrsgb5C8Zp2HQlsBClSCZhrkqbw07wVP6PXxu8bTeX85QiM9sbZCsGUasRi0caCa5TR5A87ToDBLdhC6JcQ4Z2okmQHkj9J2bR7C%2F1XDdxSELZwmF0PoK%2B%2FGnXxlz30E8FULrZ%2FJQ2UjnY4ffDWWO4myYhBTWJKl%2FpG8svsTgJLkbXw3a0V6w1iPgLWpymHoxwHJZF%2FqIEabvx9RZMvaRtPC84A%2B2dNzcua%2FpyDBNCzomv1xrNaEfu5uabNx%2BiO1KXsE5W%2FtRrUXPC595tud8agFNC85d8eCA0n5rvnoOHisUYz%2Fij8QwVgbLU%3DPaid for by Friends of Mark Warner

body: Tina for Oregon [https://nvlupin.blob.core.windows.net/images/van/NGP/NGP12/1/92654/images/TinaForOregon-Logo-FullColor-white.png] Hi Peter, it’s Janelle Bynum. I’ve really enjoyed hitting the campaign trail and meeting with voters who are fired up and ready to win this race. We’re one step closer to flipping OR-05 and taking back the House. But here's the bad news : We’re up against millions of dollars in spending by deep-pocketed Republicans. My opponent, Lori Chavez-DeRemer, is backed by Republican special interest groups who are willing to spend whatever it takes to hold this seat. As they put more money into this race, we need a flood of support to fight back and make sure we’re not getting drowned out on the airwaves. That's why I'm personally asking: Will you split a donation between Tina Kotek and me today to help us keep our ads on the air and continue to reach undecided voters? name: Pramila Jayapal
subject: A moment of light and possibility 🎇
body: [https://act.pramilaforcongress.com/go/892?refcode=em20241101-4478-footer&t;=1001&akid;=4478%2E420207%2EstGsbt]Pramila Jayapal Peter, This week, South Asians across the world arecelebrating Diwali, a festival that speaks to the deepest hopes of ourcommunity. Also known as the Festival of Lights, it’s a moment ofillumination, of connection, and of profound possibility. And this year, itjust so happens to coincide with an election in which we’ll have the chance toelect the first-ever South Asian as President of the United States. [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/pj-email-20241101-2?refcode=em20241101-4478&refcode2;=4478_420207_stGsbt&akid;=4478%2E420207%2EstGsbt][IMG] On election night in 2016, Kamala Harris and I broke barriers together.I became the first South Asian woman ever elected to the House ofRepresentatives, and she became the first South Asian woman ever elected tothe Senate. Now we stand at the brink of an even more transformative moment.It’s not just a political milestone. It's a testament to the journey ofgenerations of people who have worked, dreamed, and persevered to get us tothis moment. Our community's story is one of resilience — of voices thatrefuse to be dimmed and of traditions that continue to shine brightly acrosscontinents. We see this in the vibrant celebrations happening in homes andcommunities across the nation. In the glow of clay lamps, in the warmth ofshared meals, in the sparkle of joy that connects us. To our diverse SouthAsian community — Hindus, Muslims, Sikhs, Christians, Jains — this is a momentto honor our collective strength. To recognize the challenges we face, thefears that sometimes shadow our experiences, and also the power we have touplift, to support, and to create meaningful change. As we gather with familyand friends, let us recommit ourselves to a future of true belonging. Whereevery voice matters, where every story is heard, where our collective lightcan transform our shared landscape. [ https://secure.actblue.com/donate/pj-email-20241101-2?refcode=em20241101-4478amount=3&refcode2;=4478_420207_stGsbt&akid;=4478%2E420207%2EstGsbt]If you’re with us in the fight to build that future, consider splitting adonation between my campaign and Kamala Harris today. We need your support toget out the vote and elect the first South Asian president on Tuesday. [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/pj-email-20241101-2?amount=3&refcode;=em20241101-4478&refcode2;=4478_420207_stGsbt&akid;=4478%2E420207%2EstGsbt]Contribute From my home to yours, Happy Diwali, Peter. With hope andsolidarity, Pramila Jayapal Contribute to Pramila Jayapal:https://secure.actblue.com/donate/pj-email-footer?refcode=em20241101-4478-footer&t;=1002&refcode2;=4478_420207_stGsbt&akid;=4478%2E420207%2EstGsbtThis email was sent to dpwillis67@gmail.com. Email is the most important wayfor us to reach you about opportunities to get involved. If you need to removeyourself from our email list, click here to unsubscribe: You can unsubscribefrom this mailing list at any time:http://act.pramilaforcongress.com/cms/unsubscribe/unsubscribe/?akid=4478%2E420207%2EstGsbtPaid for by Pramila for Congress.

name: David Pan
subject: Changing our system one step at a time
body: Help me to transform our relation to government                           [1]Hopefully, you have learned about my plan to phase out our welfare andentitlement programs to replace them with a universal basic income of $16,000per year for everyone 21 and over. Even if you don’t agree with all thedetails, we need to start discussing solutions to the problems that my planwill solve: a dysfunctional welfare system, the looming insolvency of SocialSecurity and Medicare, and our mounting national debt. Right now, I am theonly one even attempting to think about these crucial issues and offering apossible plan. It is of course an ambitious plan, and things will obviouslynot change overnight, and if elected I would only be able to take the firststeps toward the discussions that would lead to such solutions. But with yoursupport, I can start on the work of turning our country around. Without it, wewill have to wait that much longer to have these discussions, and meanwhileour debts will keep increasing, making solutions that much more difficult toimplement. Please add your voice to mine so that we can start on the processof real transformation that will change all of our lives, returning to us ourfreedom and prosperity. If you have not voted, please do so. Please alsoconsider a donation to my campaign. My ads have begun running on southernCalifornia TV stations, on streaming video, through text messages, and throughsocial media. You can also see my ad on my website at DavidPanforCongress.com[2]. Now is the time that I need your help to achieve these goals for you andyour family. Help me by contributing $5, $10, $100, which can go directly intospreading my message more broadly on these platforms. name: Theresa Boisseau
subject: Second Chance - Free Viewing of Zurawski v Texas
body: I HIGHLY recommend you watch this documentary this weekend. View this email inyour browser (https://mailchi.mp/987033b5a265/amanda-zurawski-vs-texas-12709419?e=ebba716312) https://www.theresa4texas.com Hi Friend, ** Ifyou didn't get a chance to watch the documentary, Zurawski v Texas, I HIGHLYrecommend you watch it this weekend.------------------------------------------------------------ ** The Center forReproductive Rights sums it up:------------------------------------------------------------ "In the newdocumentary feature film Zurawski v Texas, independent filmmakers Maisie Crowand Abbie Perrault show the stark and terrifying reality of what it means tobe pregnant in a U.S. state that has banned abortion—and the bravery, grit anddetermination that it takes to speak out. Crow and Perrault followed threeTexas women who were denied medically necessary abortion care—Amanda Zurawski,Samantha Casiano, and Dr. Austin Dennard—as they brought their stories andbattled their case up to the Texas Supreme Court, with the help of the Centerfor Reproductive Rights’ Senior Staff Attorney Molly Duane." Watch Zurawski vTexas for free Nov 2 and 3 here(https://watch.eventive.org/togetherfilms/play/670db1d13a247100e803df13/670db1dc3f8905002cc42691)** If you are able to give, I am sure the Center for Reproductive Rights coulduse your donation.------------------------------------------------------------ Donate the theCenter for Reproductive Rights here (https://reproductiverights.org/) Theyhave cases across the country and could use our support while they fightagainst the extreme abortion bans that put women's lives in jeopardy. ** Ifyou haven't voted yet, today is the last day of early voting and Tuesday isElection Day. ------------------------------------------------------------Thanks for your help. ** Onwards,------------------------------------------------------------ ** Theresa------------------------------------------------------------ Donate(https://secure.actblue.com/donate/abrighterfuturefortexas) Volunteer(https://www.theresa4texas.com/get-involved) Issues(https://www.theresa4texas.com/what-theresa-stands-for) Shop(https://store.theresa4texas.com) https://www.theresa4texas.com Follow me onsocial media - and share with your friends and family!https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=61552530122152https://www.instagram.com/theresa4texas https://www.twitter.com/theresa4texashttps://tiktok.com/theresa4texashttps://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyd_ZE7lgKTjDchvDRg4A9g Pol. body: https://secure.actblue.com/donate/loc_lbr_fr_q42024 [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/loc_lbr_fr_q42024] Hey folks – it’s Gretchen Whitmer, the governor of Michigan. As we get closer to Election Day, I wanted to shine a light on Lisa Blunt Rochester, the Congresswoman from Delaware. Right now, she is in a heated race to become Delaware’s next Senator. In a minute, I’ll explain why you should chip in to support Lisa’s historic campaign. [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/loc_lbr_fr_q42024] SUPPORT LISA → [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/loc_lbr_fr_q42024] Lisa’s career as a public servant epitomizes the definition of what it means to be a leader and champion for everyone. Time and time again, she has helped create and pass meaningful legislation to build up our middle class, protect our seniors, and defend our voting and reproductive rights. In short, Lisa’s mission of Bright Hope is one she hopes to bring to the Senate. But her self-funding opponent would rather spend nearly a million dollars to keep his campaign afloat and defend the overturning of Roe. I wish I was joking on that last point. The scary thing about all of this is that Delaware will be crucial to the Democrats’ hopes of protecting their Senate majority. With a one-seat majority on the line, we need to do everything we can to lock this seat down and make Lisa the first Black and woman senator from Delaware. Folks – Election Day will be here before you know it. And in order to stop Trump, Vance, and Project 2025, we need to support Lisa Blunt Rochester by chipping in $10 or more to her campaign today. Right now, I am theonly one even attempting to think about these crucial issues and offering apossible plan. It is of course an ambitious plan, and things will obviouslynot change overnight, and if elected I would only be able to take the firststeps toward the discussions that would lead to such solutions. But with yoursupport, I can start on the work of turning our country around. Without it, wewill have to wait that much longer to have these discussions, and meanwhileour debts will keep increasing, making solutions that much more difficult toimplement. Please add your voice to mine so that we can start on the processof real transformation that will change all of our lives, returning to us ourfreedom and prosperity. If you have not voted, please do so. Please alsoconsider a donation to my campaign. My ads have begun running on southernCalifornia TV stations, on streaming video, through text messages, and throughsocial media. You can also see my ad on my website at DavidPanforCongress.com[2]. Now is the time that I need your help to achieve these goals for you andyour family. Help me by contributing $5, $10, $100, which can go directly intospreading my message more broadly on these platforms. You can go toDavidPanforCongress.com [2] to contribute and raise your voice to join mine.Thank you for your support! www.DavidPanForCongress.com [3] Paid for by DavidPan for Congress 2024 [3] unsubscribe [4] 3843 S. subject: I am kindly asking folks like you to chip in for the first time today. Will you make a $47 contribution to elect Kamala and Tim and defeat Trump?
body: We can turn the page on the chaos and division of Donald Trump. | | |                                                                                                                                    --- ![Harris forPresident](https://actionnetwork.org/user_files/user_files/000/111/764/original/HFP-Walz-SingleColor-HarrisBlue.png) ![](https://actionnetwork.org/s3_files/uploads/data/000/950/644/original/gwen_walz_square.jpg) Four days, Peter. Just four days to determine the next four years. **We can turn the page on the chaos and division of Donald Trump -- but not without your help reaching every last voter and getting them to the polls.** So I am kindly asking folks like you to chip in for the first time today. Will you make a $47 contribution to elect Kamala and Tim and defeat Trump? It wasn’t that many weeks ago when Tim got a call -- _the call_ \-- from Vice President Harris asking him to join this ticket. Ever since then, it’s been a whirlwind. I have traveled across the country meeting all different kinds of voters: proud Democrats who vote frequently, folks who are still deciding, folks who don’t vote in every election -- and yes, Republicans. **Everywhere I go, people are fed up with Donald Trump and fired up for Kamala and Tim’s new way forward.** But I won’t mince words, Peter. We remain the underdogs in this race. Nothing less than our very democracy is at stake. And we must win. In an election as close as this one, grassroots supporters like you will make the difference. name: AOC
subject: I’ll tell you what I believe:
body: [1]Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez for Congress We live in a constant state ofinjustice. We are always struggling against systems of mass incarceration, ofextreme income inequality, of late stage capitalism. Those conditions doexist. But one thing that I think is important is that we must mobilize for anaffirmative vision for this country — we can’t just mobilize on fear. We needto be clear about what the stakes are. We do. But I don’t believe in a ‘fearonly’ approach. I’ll tell you what I believe: I believe in a bare minimum. $15minimum wage needed to be passed several years ago. I believe in guaranteed,improved, and expanded Medicare to every single American. We can’t give up.I’ve been in that place when I was a waitress. I did spend some time giving upand being cynical and saying, “F*ck this.” And you know what it got us?Nothing. Depression, cynicism, and a sense of purposelessness. Giving up is aprivilege that people just can’t afford. Movements wax and wane. And there aretimes when it feels like our power is waning, and it’s really easy to take ourball and go home. But the strength of a movement really depends on thedurability of it, and the commitment to it. That black pill of cynicism is thedeath of movements, not the birth of them. In solidarity, Alexandria [https://act.ocasiocortez.com/go/14659?c0=aoc-email-20241101.DCJTFE&refcode;=em20241101-7501-P_FND_RES_GND&amounts;=5%2C20%2C50%2C100%2C250%2C500%2C1000&t;=1001&akid;=7501%2E2526796%2ERSo1sN]Help us continue the fight by making a grassroots donation. Email is the mostimportant way we keep in touch with people like you, so thank you for readingto the end. Small donors like you keep us going. To contribute via check,please address to Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez for Congress, PO Box 680080,Corona, NY 11368. name: Rebecca Cooke
subject: The good and the bad:
body: Peter, I wanted to update you on where things stand in WI-03 with somepositive news and some more concerning developments. But first, I have to ask:will you chip in to help us reach our final pre-election goal of raising$20,000 from grassroots supporters? We’re starting off well, but still have aways to go over the next couple of days.Donate>>https://secure.actblue.com/donate/cooke-q4-2024?refcode=em-11.2.24-all-1-aNow, the good news: We have an ever-so-slight lead in the latest polls in ourrace. Plus, election analysts have shifted the race slightly in our favor.These updates show the momentum we’ve built throughout this people-poweredcampaign. And I’m thankful for every single supporter who helped us get tothis point. But we can’t get complacent, Peter, because here’s the bad news:We are being heavily outspent by Derrick Van Orden and his extremist, deep-pocketed allies and super PACs. They’ve just doubled their ad buys in the mostcompetitive media markets in WI-03. That’s concerning because we need to winthose communities to prevail in three days. Here’s the bottom line: we need asurge of grassroots support NOW to counter Van Orden’s ad push and big-dollardonors as we enter the final stretch of this race. Will you contributewhatever you can today to help flip WI-03? What matters most is that we get asmany people donating as we can, because it adds up fast. Donate >>https://secure.actblue.com/donate/cooke-q4-2024?refcode=em-11.2.24-all-1-aThank you, Peter. Your support will help us win in three days. name: Carville, James
subject: Every single Democrat NEEDS to pay attention to Sherrod's Senate race RIGHT NOW
body: Friend, I'm about to ask you to chip in every dollar you can to help SherrodBrown win in Ohio and defend our Democratic Senate majority – but first, letme explain why this is so damn important for ALL of us. But hell, if you wantto click here and chip in right away, I'm not gonna stop you.https://secure.actblue.com/contribute/page/sherrod-brown-email-wr-24?amounts=250,100,50,25,5&refcode;=jtk3725-fr-text I'll get right into it:Democrats have a razor-thin Senate majority, and we're facing a NIGHTMARESenate map. There's a strong chance it will all come down to Ohio, which meansSherrod is the ONLY thing standing between us and a Republican Senate. Friend,I've worked on campaigns for a long time. I've been on the winning side andthe losing side. If there's one thing I know, it's that money makes a BIGdifference. I wish it weren't the case, but it is. TV ads, phone banks, yardsigns, campaign events in every corner of the state – it all adds up FAST.That's why I'm so terrified right now. If this were a simple battle betweengood and evil, I wouldn't be worried – Sherrod is as good a leader as Ohioanshave ever had. He fights harder for workers than anybody I know, and he's notafraid to take on the big banks and corporations that are making things harderfor the middle class. But money muddies the waters, and his opponent has got aton of it. He's poured A TON into his own campaign, and there's a lot morewhere that came from. Sherrod simply doesn't have that kind of money – sothat's where this grassroots team needs to come in and have his back, friend.I know Sherrod can win this critical race and keep the Senate blue, but ONLYIF we all come together to give him the resources he needs. So I'm asking:Will you rush $5, $25, or even $50 to help him win in Ohio and defend ourSenate majority? https://secure.actblue.com/contribute/page/sherrod-brown-email-wr-24?amounts=250,100,50,25,5&refcode;=jtk3725-fr-text Thanks for doingyour part – there's simply no other option if we want to save the Senate! –James Carville -------- This email was sent to dpwillis67@gmail.com. name: Tim Walz
subject: Let’s leave it all out on the field
body: Folks, this is Tim Walz. I couldn't be prouder to be on this ticket and tohelp make Kamala Harris the next president of the United States. There’s a lotmore I want to say, but before I continue, I’m hoping you’ll split acontribution between Tina Smith and our campaign today. With just four daysleft in this election, we need to leave it all out on the field. Everycontribution will make a huge difference.[https://secure.actblue.com/donate/tsm-em-harris24?email=dpwillis67@gmail.com]If you've saved your payment information with ActBlue Express, your splitdonation to Tina Smith and the Harris-Walz campaign will go throughimmediately: CHIP IN $10 NOW [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/tsm-em-harris24?express_lane=true&amount;=10&email;=dpwillis67@gmail.com] CHIP IN $25NOW [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/tsm-em-harris24?express_lane=true&amount;=25&email;=dpwillis67@gmail.com] CHIP IN $50NOW [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/tsm-em-harris24?express_lane=true&amount;=50&email;=dpwillis67@gmail.com] CHIP IN$100 NOW [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/tsm-em-harris24?express_lane=true&amount;=100&email;=dpwillis67@gmail.com] CHIP IN$250 NOW [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/tsm-em-harris24?express_lane=true&amount;=250&email;=dpwillis67@gmail.com] ANOTHERAMOUNT [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/tsm-em-harris24?email=dpwillis67@gmail.com] Growing up in a small town like Butte,Nebraska, you learn to take care of each other. The family down the road maynot think, pray, or love like you, but they are your neighbors and you lookout for them. Now we know that Donald Trump, JD Vance, and MAGA Republicanshave a different vision of America. When they talk about freedom they mean thegovernment should have the freedom to invade every corner of our life. Take itfrom a small-town guy: they know nothing about what working people need.That's not what we do in Minnesota. We don’t attack our neighbors’ rights. Wewelcome everyone in, and we lift each other up. My friend Tina Smithunderstands this. And she works hard every day to ensure Minnesotans’ voicesare heard in the United States Senate. That’s what this campaign is about:working together to build a future where everyone has the opportunity not justto get by, but to get ahead. Where workers come first, health care and housingare human rights, and the government stays the hell out of your bedroom. Butwe need you in this fight with us. Will you split a donation of $10, orwhatever works for you right now, between Tina Smith and our campaign so wecan continue working together and defend our values up and down the ballot inNovember? [https://secure.actblue.com/donate/tsm-em-harris24?email=dpwillis67@gmail.com&amount;=10] Four days to go. Let’s leaveit all on the field. name: Ted Cruz
subject: I’m standing alone
body: We’re in real trouble- here’s why We’re in real trouble- here’s why Peter,Here is the situation. Senator Chuck Schumer (D-NY) the powerful MajorityLeader for the Senate Democrats has directed his forces to inject millions andmillions of dollars into Texas to defeat me and flip Texas brightblue. Schumerhas said they will spend over one-hundred million dollars to defeat me. Otherradical leftwing groups and National Democrat Party committees are jumpinginto the fray as well-just flooding us with attack ads, flyers, and boots onthe ground… But here’s the worst part: The National Party is not coming tosave us. I am standing alone against this massive progressive onslaught. Weare getting almost NO HELP from Mitch McConnell. And the major RepublicanSenate Super PAC has no operations or ads running in Texas… That’s why I’mcalling on all grassroots conservatives from Maine to Marfa for help… RUSHHELP HERE >> The Washington DC Party Establishment doesn’t want a grassrootsconservative like me in the Senate- they never have, and their lack of helpduring the fight of my life is proof! I need YOUR help. Not because ourfundraising hasn’t been successful- we’re doing well, and thousands of Texansand patriots from all over are stepping in to give generously. Many are givingfor the very first time, while others have given every month this year. Butwith no air cover. I'm forced to ask for urgent help. We can’t lose Texas- andright now we’re in real trouble. STAND WITH TEXAS & SAVE AMERICA RIGHT NOW >>Thank you for standing with me. Ted Cruz DONATE >> Paid for by Ted Cruz forSenate 815 A Brazos, PMB 550, Austin, TX 78701 Unsubscribe

name: Adam Schiff
subject: Trump called me “total scum”
body: [ https://act.adamschiff.com/go/62?t=1001&akid;=8121%2E5257348%2EnSb5EY ]Adam Schiff for Senate Derek, stop me if you’ve heard this before: Donald Trump’s campaign claims that he’s a serious candidate, taking the rally stage to defend his record and talk about his agenda. But he gets introduced by racist, sexist, divisive speakers. Who ramble almost as much as he does. When Trump takes the stage, he launches into an incoherent, meandering speech, lacking in policy proposals, and chock full of lies and attacks against his political opponents, including me. [ https://act.adamschiff.com/go/2907?c0=nov2024_abs_em.SALZ0e&refcode;=AU_ABS_FR_GEN_RES_AC90_20241101_PM1_V1_S1&email;=&t;=1004&akid;=8121%2E5257348%2EnSb5EY ]That’s exactly what happened yesterday at his rally in New Mexico. Derek, the attacks don’t phase me anymore, but with precious little time left for undecided voters to make their decisions at the ballot box, we can’t let their final impression of me come from a Trump screed. Please rush a contribution to boost our voter outreach in the final days of this election. body: Friend, I have a big favor to ask: If just 5% of folks reading this email chipped in $5, we would hit our $500,000 goal in no time. Can I count on you to step up with a split donation of $10 today to ensure my team and I have the resources we need to push back against the $40 million worth of attack ads Ted Cruz and his allies are running against us right now? https://secure.actblue.com/donate/gfs_colinallred?refcode=jtk5609-bu-text&amounts;=5,25,50,100,250 Last time around, Ted Cruz won his race by just over 2% of the vote – that was a difference of about 215,000 votes, friend. But despite being closer than ever to defeating Ted, we've still got a lot more work to do and only a handful of days left to do it. I know seeing a number like $500,000 can feel overwhelming, but if thousands of hardworking folks like you chip in $5 here, $25 there, and the occasional $100, we will be able to collectively reach this critical goal. name: Sent from Debbie's iPhone
subject: Just poured myself a cup — can we check in?
body: Good morning, friend — I just poured myself a cup of coffee and am eager towrite to you and get my day going! 🌞 I'll be honest: I need a lot of coffeethese days, and it's because I'm not sleeping much. Everything is OK, it'sjust that I'm a bundle of nerves and excitement in these final days of thecampaign, where we are so close to actually defeating Rick Scott andprotecting Democratic control of the Senate! I need you to know that we neverwould have gotten to a point where the polls are statistically tied, wherebrand new polling data has me leading by 18 points with independent voters,where Rick Scott is forced to spend tens of millions of dollars to competewith our grassroots movement, and where the major Democratic committees spendmillions of dollars of their own money to help us because they believe in us!Thank you, friend. A year ago at this time, the political pundits wrote offFlorida completely. We put Florida in play. We gave Rick Scott his notice. Weare on the cusp of pulling off the greatest political upset in modern history.But Rick Scott is outspending me nearly 3-to-1 on the airwaves — and he'salready spent over $38 million on ads to defeat me. Well, I don't have afraudulently earned fortune like him to tap into. I have you, friend. I havethis grassroots movement. And I can only fight back and win by closing in onmy final $4 million goal before Election Day. So please, will you make adonation of $5 or more to help me make history here in Florida? Whatever yougive will be put to work immediately to counter Rick Scott's attack ads,defeat him once and for all, and save our Democratic Senate majority!https://secure.actblue.com/contribute/page/mw_dmp_2024_email_fr?amounts=5,25,50,100,250&refcode;=jtk2478-fr-text Well, there's another cup of coffee gone ☕️. I hope you have a great day,friend. I'll check in with you again soon! Debbie -------- This email was sentto dpwillis67@gmail.com. name: Hung Cao
subject: The end of the road
body: Fellow Patriot, I’m afraid we could be at the end of the road. I don’t mean tobe too negative, but Tim Kaine has a MASSIVE war chest, and I just don’t knowif we can overcome it. This is CAPT Hung Cao. I’m not a career politician likeTim Kaine. I’m a husband, a father, and a 25-year combat Naval Captain. I’malso running for Senate in what could be the biggest political upset inVirginia’s history I’m running against a 30+ year incumbent who has spent hisentire life serving Washington's special interests. Let’s just cut to thechase: I can’t do this alone. Can you pitch in to support my campaign? PITCHIN NOW I won’t lie, this is going to be an uphill battle, but I know thatwith you on our A-Team we can win this seat and take back the Senate. Our teamis gearing up for the upset of the century, and we want YOU to be a part ofit.Please, will you pitch in now to make sure we have the resources we need towin? SAVE OUR COUNTRY My wife and I are raising our children to grow up intohonest men and women, so you can trust that I’ll keep my promise to put ourCommonwealth and our country first in everything I do. In Liberty, CAPT HungCao USN (Ret) Paid for by Hung Cao for Virginia Use of military rank, jobtitles, and photographs in uniform does not imply endorsement by theDepartment of the Navy or the Department of Defense. name: Jon Favreau
subject: We need to do everything we can to make sure Bob wins
body: Jon Favreau here. If you’re way too online like me, you’ve probably seen a tonof headlines about a bunch of rich guys running for Senate in states wherethey don't even live. Connecticut mega-millionaire David McCormick is one ofthose rich guys, and he’s running against beloved Pennsylvania Senator, BobCasey. So look, this will be a very close race, and we need to do everythingwe can to make sure Bob wins — [ https://secure.actblue.com/donate/casey-em-20241101-2?refcode=em20241101-2&refcode2;=4745_552475_IPLfG2&akid;=4745%2E552475%2EIPLfG2]which is why I’m asking if you’ll contribute $5 towards his campaign today.David McCormick is a former Wall Street hedge-fund exec who wants you to thinkhe grew up on a Pennsylvania farm, which is only true if you think that livingin a mansion 10 minutes down the road from a farm where your family raisedArabian horses counts as “growing up on a farm.” But wait, Peter, there'smore: McCormick also thinks the most popular beer in Pennsylvania is called“YANG-ling,” which is like running for Senate in Massachusetts and saying youwant coffee from "DOON-kin’ Donuts." If it wasn’t obvious before, it’s crystalclear now: David McCormick is wrong for Pennsylvania. But this will be one ofthe toughest races of the year for Democrats. McCormick has millions uponmillions of dollars of his own to dump into this race, in addition to thebacking of Donald Trump and billionaire-funded super PACs. Pennsylvania is ascompetitive as it gets, and with the Senate majority and the White Housedepending on it, we can’t take anything for granted. name: #6 Steve Garvey
subject: The most important week
body: What matters most right now is that we do whatever we can to fund a campaignthat can win. That’s the most important thing. Winning this race.                                                                                                                  Fellow Patriot,I have an important message that I didn’t think I’d be sending you today. Injust a moment, I am going to ask you to make a contribution to my campaign forU.S. Senate. November 5th isdays away, and I’d really appreciate the chance toexplain why this request — especially today — is so critically important.Here’s the truth: Right now, we have a week of media buys to pay for — themost important week of the entire campaign. And if we don’t raise what we neednow, we will be forced to give up the airwaves and let Adam Schiff and theDemocrat-machine backing him up run their attacks on me unopposed. Whatmatters most right now is that we do whatever we can to fund a campaign thatcan win. That’s the most important thing. Winning this race. Not just for thesake of winning, but because of what it would mean to substitute my presencewith Adam Schiff’s in the Senate. That’s a reality I don’t think any of uswant to consider, but it’s what will happen if we come up short. Now, time isrunning out. So, this is the part where I ask, one more time, and very humbly:Can you please use this link to make a donation to my campaign for U.S. Senatein California before Election Day? These emails are how we fund our campaign,and I really need you to chip in and help prevent us from falling behind.DONATE $35 DONATE $100 DONATE $500 DONATE $50 DONATE $250 DONATE $1000DONATE $35 DONATE $50 DONATE $100 DONATE $250 DONATE $500 DONATE $1000OTHER AMOUNT Thank you Fellow Patriot, and God bless, DONATE <> PAID FOR BYSTEVE GARVEY FOR U.S. SENATE PO Box 532389 Los Angeles, CA 90053-2389Unsubscribe here

name: Liz Walters, ODP Chair
subject: Tuesday will be here before we know it.
body: I want to say thank you, team. Every time we’ve sent out the call for help tothis grassroots movement, you’ve answered. You’ve donated. You’ve knocked ondoors and made phone calls to voters in your free time. You’ve helped usregister Ohioans all across the state. You’ve talked to your friends andfamily about this historic election. It means more than you know. Now, here weare in November, with the election looming over us, only four days away – andwe have a new goal that we need your help to reach. We intend to raise $25,000by Election Day so we can fight back against the onslaught of Republicanspending trying to silence our voices and buy this election. Can you pitch in$5 to help us reach this goal? https://secure.actblue.com/donate/odp-email-241101-gotv?amount=5&refcode;=ODP_ATA_EM_FR_ThankYou_241101_T1_1 Inthese next four days, we’re not giving up on our unprecedented get out thevote push. We’re still on the ground, mobilizing voters, and getting Ohioansto the polls. subject: No one has ever regretted getting off the sidelines
body: Peter, I’m an actress, director, singer, longtime activist, and, above all, acitizen of our great democracy. And as a citizen with a platform larger thanmost, I believe it is not only my right but also my duty to express myconcerns. So here goes Peter: I’m concerned by what I’m seeing in Pennsylvaniaand national Republicans’ ruthless efforts to unseat Bob Casey and flip thisbattleground red. If the GOP succeeds in flipping Pennsylvania red, they’llalmost certainly regain control of both the Senateand the White House,threatening everything from voting rights to women’s rights to the fightagainst climate change. That’s why outside interest groups have startedspending upwards of $150 million to defeat Bob. The stakes this November arehigher than ever before.So before I go on, can you please split a donationbetween Bob’s re-election campaign and Defeat Boebert PAC? DONATE NOW >> I’mcommitted to electing lawmakers like Bob Casey, who believes that everyonedeserves a fair shot at getting ahead and staying ahead. Bob’s opponent on theother hand is a Connecticut mega-millionaire who will do and say anything tohelp his own bottom line. With the most extreme Republican party of mylifetime teetering on the edge of regaining power, we need all hands on deck.If we’re going to protect our Senate majority and the White House, we must allstay informed and stay involved.
